## 8-Phase Implementation Order

```
Phase 0 — Foundation (Tailwind + shadcn + fonts + ThemeProvider)
    ↓
Phase 1 — Shell (sidebar, top bar, layout, routing structure)
    ↓
Phase 2 — Shared components (configure all shadcn components + custom patterns)
    ↓
Phase 3 — Auth (login + signup)
    ↓
Phase 4 — Core pages (overview, users, sessions, memory)
    ↓
Phase 5 — Graph domain (graph explorer, communities, facts + D3.js setup)
    ↓
Phase 6 — Analytics & Monitoring (charts, health, Prometheus query)
    ↓
Phase 7 — Admin & System (API keys, schemas, classifications, extractions, audit, settings)
    ↓
Phase 8 — Polish (animations, empty/error states, keyboard shortcuts, a11y, build)
```

---

## Key Design Decisions

1. **D3.js for graphs** — raw `d3-force` simulation + `d3-selection` for rendering. More control, smaller bundle, and we can customize every aspect (node shapes, link curves, glow effects). The previous `react-force-graph-2d` was a wrapper over D3 anyway — we just cut out the middle layer.

2. **tremor for charts** — gives us shadcn/Tailwind-native chart components. AreaChart for daily trends, BarChart for comparisons, DonutChart for distributions. All theme-aware through Tailwind classes.

3. **sonner for toasts** — shadcn's recommended toast library. Minimal, stackable, dark-theme-compatible. Replaces the current `NotificationProvider` pattern.

4. **next-themes for dark/light** — handles system preference detection, localStorage persistence, flash-free SSR. Replaces the custom `MuiProvider` + `ThemeContext`.

5. **Sub-pages for classifications/extractions** — instead of 5 crowded tabs in the session detail page, keep the 3 main tabs (Messages, Facts, Graph) and link to classifications/extractions as sub-pages. This keeps the session detail focused and gives each feature its own space.

